Temitope Balogun Joshua, founder of The Synagogue, Church Of All Nations (SCOAN) is rumoured dead. A family source told Peoples Gazette that he died in Lagos on Saturday evening shortly after concluding a programme at his church. The renowned gospel preacher known globally for his prophecies and healing of the sick as well as casting out of demons is rumoured dead at the age of 57. DAILY POST could not confirm his death at this time and there is no official report from his Church or family confirming his death. Nigeria’ll not break up – Prophet TB Joshua responds to Kanu, Igboho’s secession calls But his friend and former Aviation Minister, Femi Fani-Kayode referred to the report as fake, stating that the acclaimed man of God is alive and well. “The story that is being peddled around by some fake news merchants that my dearest friend and brother, Prophet T.B. Joshua of SCOAN, is dead is FALSE! “It is FAKE NEWS in its most hideous form. The Prophet is alive and well and he shall live long and prosper. Glory hallelujah!” he wrote. At the moment, it is not clear if the prophet is dead or alive. Details later.
